## Attaching a NSG to a Datacenter

A single Network Security Group can be attached at any time to a Datacenter. To do this, use the <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`ionoscloud.nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`ionoscloud.nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`" pulumi-lang-go="`nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`" pulumi-lang-python="`nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`ionoscloud.nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`" pulumi-lang-java="`ionoscloud.nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`" pulumi-lang-hcl="`ionoscloud_datacenter_nsg_selection`">`ionoscloud.nsg.DatacenterNsgSelection`</span> and provide the IDs of the NSG and Datacenter to link them. 
Deleting the resource or setting the empty string for the <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`nsgId`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`NsgId`" pulumi-lang-go="`nsgId`" pulumi-lang-python="`nsg_id`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`nsgId`" pulumi-lang-java="`nsgId`" pulumi-lang-hcl="`nsg_id`">`nsgId`</span> field will de-attach any previously linked NSG from the Datacenter.

